questiontext.text:
Put the Thames back together and then locate the following famous landmarks:

  • The Cutty Sark
  • St Paul's Cathedral
  • The Houses of Parliament
  • The Tower of London
  • The London Eye.

This is an example of the Drag and drop onto image question type.It also uses grouped images.

Drag the words relating to each type of geography to the correct notepad.

This is an example of a Drag and drop marker question type. In this example, several markers can be dropped into the same region.

Drag the correct names to the correct regions of Australia. Position the marker where you want by using the little circle in the top left corner.

This is an example of a Drag and drop marker question type.

Drag the capital city onto the correct country.There are a few extra just to confuse you!

This is an example of a Drag and drop into text question type.

The capital of England is [[1]] which is fairly easy. But do you know that the capital of Wales is [[2]]?

Scotland's capital city is the very beautiful [[3]] while the Republic of Ireland has [[4]] as its capital and Northern Ireland's capital is [[5]]

Do you know your Great Britain from your United Kingdom and your British Isles? Find out here!

This question uses the Select missing words question type. 

****************************************************

Scotland, England and [[1]] together form  [[2]]

Together with [[3]] they also make up  [[4]]

So what are the British Isles? They are [[4]] and [[5]], together with many other islands and dependencies such as [[6]].

correctfeedback.text: Well done! You know your UK from your GB!

partiallycorrectfeedback.text: Not quite  - you are almost there

incorrectfeedback.text: No - perhaps you should google the terms first and then try to answer.
